ughout Archty's life, and they should each be released about two months after the prior chapter.\n\nThere is one aspect of \u201cThe Archetype\u201d that is unique in my experience; the cursor. It isn\u2019t dead center, it floats on the screen based on the movement of Archty, and how his POV changes. It\u2019s an interesting choice, but in a game this dark (figuratively and literally) it becomes frustrating to locate the dark cursor against a dark background, with only an edge lit for contrast. Easier with time and practice.\n\nThere are some aspects of the game potential buyers of \u201cThe Archetype\u201d need to know. First, there currently is no means by which to adjust screen brightness, and that\u2019s deliberate (and significant to the atmosphere.) This is so significant that the DEVs actually recommend that the game ONLY be played in the dark. Since not all gamers have this option, it must be considered sooner, rather than later. It also might seem to fail to take into consideration different PCs baselines, the changes in brightness when playing with battery power, and differences in vision (such as with age. I have one game with eight settings for colorblindness alone), but perhaps not, as the DEVS seem very deliberate in all things. There have been discussions about a slider to compensate for these numerous variables, as is commonly used in games. (\"The Archetype\" has only been out for a matter of days at this point, so do doubt numerous positive changes are yet to be made.) On a separate topic, please be aware that there has also been an issue concerning a genuine 911 call used in the game WITH PERMISSION. That is no longer a concern, as a suitable replacement has been made.\n\nThe first time one tries to save \u201cThe Archetype\u201d gamers will learn that the feature will not be available until a certain point in the game is reached by the player, and that will likely be after a minimum of an hour of game time. I\u2019ve played 3 - 4 hours (offline, mostly), died 6 \u2013 8 times and haven\u2019t reached that point yet. Also, at this time there is no PAUSE feature (though it is being discussed), so the game will continue while you answer the door or check the baby. At some points in the game the issue is minimal, at others, significant. (Again, in discussion.)\n\nBut \u201cfear not!\u201d (except where appropriate, of course), the DEVs of \u201cThe Archetype\u201d are very attentive and concerned about their game. Even in just a few days, the number of ideas and suggestions from many gamers that have been responded to is quite reassuring. There have been updates EVERY 2 - 3 days. There seems to be an excellent possibility that \u201cThe Archetype\u201d will turn out to be a very special game.\n\nEDIT: Having completed Chapter One, I can say that in retrospect, it's fairly simple (except for one action that I don't believe is in any way intuitive, and is counter to every other similar action in the game, but can be found in the correct Youtube walkthrough.) And there seems to be no means of saving, only of completion, which I presume counts as a \"save\" for the complete, four-part game.\n\n(As with most Steam games, offline game time is not tracked.)", "received_for_free": false, "timestamp_created": 1442794333, "written_during_early_access": false, "timestamp_updated": 1442969504, "recommendationid": "18125828", "language": "english", "votes_down": 19, "steam_purchase": true, "weighted_vote_score": "0.530321", "voted_up": true}, {"author": {"last_played": 1450923026, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "num_reviews": 25, "playtime_forever": 18, "steamid": "76561198014454061", "num_games_owned": 590}, "votes_funny": 2, "votes_up": 11, "comment_count": 0, "review": "In it's current state it's more of a early access. if you have multiple monitors then stay away since the mouse does not lock and you will find yourself constantly clicking out of the game and breaking \"immersion\". They need to add some kinda window loc