luded schizophrenia and yet portrayed people with schizophrenia poorly, either by making them automatically cloudcookoolander or exaggerating them. This work treated the subject well, as well as including another condition, General Anxiety Disorder. All of this felt treated respectfully and accurately, which is a well done to the developers.\n\nRecently I emailed the devs. and discovered a lot of the aspects that I thought of as bugs were actually features, added in such a way that they're not-obvious, but clear once you think about it. Of course, when you're running in fear, you can't exactly stop to think, which acts to that tension. As well as this though, the devs are extremely respondent to player wishes. I've read online several mentions of changes that have been made due to player wishes before I bought this game, and there's already talks of further updates. This game isn't early access level, but it is still being refined.\n\nNow, the game isn't perfect. It can be bumpy at steps. There may some mild glitches that affect gameplay;  However, the dev is quick to respond to any reports. Despite some annoyance and frustration, I would recommend this game to anybody looking for a good horror game with a rich storyline. I'm currently planning to explore the game again for Easter Eggs and alternative options in certain encounters, of which a fair few exist.", "received_for_free": false, "timestamp_created": 1444282459, "written_during_early_access": false, "timestamp_updated": 1444282459, "recommendationid": "18378898", "language": "english", "votes_down": 10, "steam_purchase": true, "weighted_vote_score": "0.502717", "voted_up": true}, {"author": {"last_played": 1481490765, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "num_reviews": 7, "playtime_forever": 433, "steamid": "76561198128133321", "num_games_owned": 123}, "votes_funny": 0, "votes_up": 1, "comment_count": 0, "review": "Are there any walkthroughs available for chapter 3?", "received_for_free": false, "timestamp_created"